'''Madrid''' is the capital and most populous city of Spain. Situated on the Manzanares river in the centre of the Iberian Peninsula, it is the political, economic, and cultural heart of the country.

The city is home to the Spanish royal family, national government institutions, and a dense concentration of museums, including the [[Museo del Prado]], the Reina Sofía, and the Thyssen-Bornemisza, which together form its renowned Golden Triangle of Art.
